{"author":"JUSTIN MARTYR","book":"Hortatory Address to the Greeks","chapter":16,"classification":{"bucket":"Patristic / broadly orthodox","canonicalStatus":"patristic","contentKind":"primary","cautionReason":"No major mainstream heresy warning is attached by the preview classifier.","doctrinalStatus":"orthodox","labels":["patristic"],"severity":0},"id":"anf01:viii.vi.xvi","lineage":["JUSTIN MARTYR","Hortatory Address to the Greeks","Chapter XVI.—Testimony of the Sibyl."],"metadata":{"author":"JUSTIN MARTYR","authorshipDateRange":null,"ccel":{"id":"anf01","sourceUrl":"https://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/anf01.xml","title":"ANF01. The Apostolic Fathers with Justin Martyr and Irenaeus"},"source":{"id":"anf01","provider":"CCEL","sourceUrl":"https://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/anf01.xml","title":"ANF01. The Apostolic Fathers with Justin Martyr and Irenaeus"}},"originalBook":null,"sourceVolumeId":"anf01","title":"Chapter XVI.—Testimony of the Sibyl.","source":{"id":"anf01","sourceUrl":"https://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/anf01.xml","title":"ANF01. The Apostolic Fathers with Justin Martyr and Irenaeus"},"verses":[{"book":"Hortatory Address to the Greeks","chapter":16,"text":"We must also mention what the ancient and exceedingly remote Sibyl, whom Plato and Aristophanes, and others besides, mention as a prophetess, taught you in her oracular verses concerning one only God.","verse":1},{"book":"Hortatory Address to the Greeks","chapter":16,"text":"And she speaks thus:—","verse":2},{"book":"Hortatory Address to the Greeks","chapter":16,"text":"Then elsewhere thus:—","verse":3},{"book":"Hortatory Address to the Greeks","chapter":16,"text":"And again somewhere else:—","verse":4},{"book":"Hortatory Address to the Greeks","chapter":16,"text":"These are the Sibyl’s words.","verse":5}]}